data.title: Steinbeck with Carl T. Rowan and Frans Eemil Silanpaa
data.meta_description: Unique materials held by San Jose State University Special Collections and Archives, the Beethoven Center, and the Steinbeck Center.
data.text:
Inscription on the back reads "John Steinbeck seated with US Ambassador to Finland Carl T. Rowan (on the left) calls on Finish writer and Nobel Prize winner Frans Eemil Sillanpaa (in the center,) Oct. 14, 1963" Sillanpaa won the Nobel Prize for Literature in 1939.

For more information on copyright or permissions for this image, please contact the Martha Heasley Cox Center for Steinbeck Studies.
